-- Skoda Auto May Boost Vehicle Sales in 2012, Vahland Tells CTK
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2012-01-10T08:53:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/skoda-auto-may-boost-vehicle-sales-in-2012-vahland-tells-ctk.html
Skoda Auto AS, the Czech unit of
 Volkswagen AG (VOW) , may sell about 959,200 vehicles this year, an
increase of 80,000 units from the previous year,  CTK  reported,
citing Chief Executive Officer Winfried Vahland.  The car-maker may sell 1 million units annually in three
years, the newswire added, citing Vahland.  Skoda Auto announced earlier it plans to reach annual sales
of 1.5 million cars by 2018.  To contact the reporter on this story: Lenka Ponikelska in
Prague   lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  